const e=[{id:"1",title:"Mould Removal: Prevention and Treatment Tips",slug:"mould-removal-prevention-treatment-tips",excerpt:"Discover the most effective strategies for identifying, removing, and preventing mould growth on your property exterior in the humid Queensland climate.",content:`
      <h2>The Queensland Mould Problem</h2>
      <p>In Queensland, high humidity and frequent rainfall create the perfect breeding ground for mould, mildew, and algae on exterior surfaces. Not only are these unsightly, but they can also cause long-term structural damage and pose health risks to your family.</p>
      <h3>Identifying Exterior Mould</h3>
      <p>Mould often starts as small black or green spots on driveways, siding, or roofs. Over time, it spreads, creating a slippery layer on walkways and degrading the paint on your home.</p>
      <h3>Professional Treatment vs. DIY</h3>
      <p>While bleach might seem like a quick fix, it often only bleaches the mould temporarily without killing the root system. Our professional soft washing and pressure cleaning methods use specialized, eco-friendly biocides that eradicate the spores completely, ensuring a longer-lasting clean.</p>
      <h3>Prevention Tips</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ensure proper drainage around your home.</li>
        <li>Trim overhanging branches to increase sunlight exposure.</li>
        <li>Schedule annual professional exterior cleaning.</li>
      </ul>
    `,featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1584622650111-993a426fbf0a?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2025-10-15",reading_time:4,related_posts:["pressure-cleaning-safety-what-you-need-to-know"],faq_schema:[{question:"Can bleach kill mould on concrete?",answer:"Bleach often only removes the color of the mould but leaves the roots intact. Professional biocides are required for complete removal."}]},{id:"2",title:"Driveway Maintenance: Keep Your Concrete Looking New",slug:"driveway-maintenance-keep-concrete-looking-new",excerpt:"A clean driveway significantly boosts curb appeal. Learn how to maintain your concrete, aggregate, or paved driveway year-round.",content:`
      <h2>Why Driveway Maintenance Matters</h2>
      <p>Your driveway is often the first thing people notice about your home. Beyond aesthetics, keeping it clean prevents deterioration from engine oil, tire marks, and invasive weeds.</p>
      <h3>Common Driveway Stains and How We Treat Them</h3>
      <p>Oil spills and rust are notorious for penetrating porous concrete. We use industrial-grade degreasers combined with hot water high-pressure surface cleaners to lift these deep-set stains safely.</p>
      <h3>Sealing Your Driveway</h3>
      <p>After a thorough clean, applying a high-quality sealant is crucial. It protects against UV fading, repels oil, and stops water from seeping in and causing cracks.</p>
    `,featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1594611372993-761f31b97dae?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2025-11-02",reading_time:5,related_posts:["how-to-prepare-your-home-for-pressure-cleaning"],faq_schema:[{question:"How often should I clean my driveway?",answer:"We recommend a professional driveway clean every 12 to 18 months to prevent permanent staining."}]},{id:"3",title:"Roof Cleaning Tips: Extend Your Roof's Lifespan",slug:"roof-cleaning-tips-extend-lifespan",excerpt:"Protect your biggest investment. Learn why soft wash roof cleaning is essential for removing lichen and moss safely.",content:"<h2>The Danger of Lichen and Moss</h2><p>Lichen and moss are not just ugly; they actively eat away at your roof tiles and colorbond. Their acidic root systems penetrate the surface, leading to premature aging and costly replacements.</p><h3>The Soft Wash Approach</h3><p>Never use high pressure on a roof! It can strip the protective coating and force water into your ceiling cavity. We use a dedicated soft wash system that applies a gentle, specialized cleaning solution to safely kill organic growth.</p>",featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1414846203799-621096642082?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2025-12-10",reading_time:6,related_posts:["seasonal-cleaning-guide-brisbane-homes"],faq_schema:[]},{id:"4",title:"Solar Panel Efficiency: Why Regular Cleaning Matters",slug:"solar-panel-efficiency-cleaning-matters",excerpt:"Are your solar panels underperforming? Dust, bird droppings, and pollution can reduce efficiency by up to 25%.",content:"<h2>Maximizing Your Solar Investment</h2><p>Solar panels need clear access to sunlight. In Queensland, dust, pollen, and bird droppings accumulate quickly. Studies show that dirty panels can lose up to 25% of their efficiency.</p><h3>Our Pure Water Cleaning Method</h3><p>Using regular tap water leaves hard water stains that block sunlight. We use a specialized pure water filtration system and soft bristled brushes to leave your panels spot-free and operating at peak performance without voiding your warranty.</p>",featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1680050977709-56ac8eb7b062?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2026-01-05",reading_time:3,related_posts:["roof-cleaning-tips-extend-lifespan"],faq_schema:[]},{id:"5",title:"Pressure Cleaning Safety: What You Need to Know",slug:"pressure-cleaning-safety-what-you-need-to-know",excerpt:"Pressure washing looks easy, but it carries significant risks. Learn why hiring an insured professional is safer for you and your property.",content:"<h2>The Risks of DIY Pressure Cleaning</h2><p>Industrial pressure washers can output water at over 4000 PSI—enough to slice through protective boots, shatter windows, and permanently scar concrete.</p><h3>Property Damage</h3><p>Using the wrong pressure or nozzle on brick, timber, or sandstone can cause irreversible damage. Our technicians are trained to adjust pressure and use appropriate chemical treatments to clean safely.</p>",featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1600596542815-ffad4c1539a9?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2026-02-20",reading_time:4,related_posts:[],faq_schema:[]},{id:"6",title:"Seasonal Cleaning Guide for Brisbane Homes",slug:"seasonal-cleaning-guide-brisbane-homes",excerpt:"A practical calendar for maintaining your home exterior throughout the harsh Queensland seasons.",content:"<h2>Pre-Summer Prep</h2><p>Before the storm season hits, ensuring your gutters and downpipes are completely clear is vital to prevent roof leaks and foundation flooding.</p><h2>Post-Summer Recovery</h2><p>After the humid months, mould and algae growth peaks. Autumn is the perfect time for a full house soft wash to kill off organic growth before it sets in for winter.</p>",featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1512917774080-9991f1c4c750?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2026-03-15",reading_time:5,related_posts:[],faq_schema:[]},{id:"7",title:"How to Prepare Your Home for Pressure Cleaning",slug:"how-to-prepare-your-home-for-pressure-cleaning",excerpt:"Simple steps to take before our technicians arrive to ensure a smooth, efficient, and safe cleaning process.",content:"<h2>Pre-Cleaning Checklist</h2><p>To ensure the best results and protect your belongings, please follow these steps before our team arrives: <ul><li>Move vehicles from the driveway.</li><li>Ensure all windows and doors are securely closed.</li><li>Relocate potted plants and sensitive outdoor furniture.</li><li>Keep pets indoors during the cleaning process.</li></ul></p>",featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1499793983690-e29da59ef1c2?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2026-04-10",reading_time:3,related_posts:[],faq_schema:[]},{id:"8",title:"Commercial Cleaning: Benefits for Your Business",slug:"commercial-cleaning-benefits-for-your-business",excerpt:"First impressions count. Discover how regular commercial exterior cleaning protects your brand image and property value.",content:"<h2>The Value of Curb Appeal</h2><p>Customers judge your business before they even step inside. A dirty storefront, stained parking lot, or algae-covered facade sends the wrong message. Regular commercial pressure cleaning ensures your property reflects the professionalism of your business.</p><h3>Safety and Compliance</h3><p>Greasy parking lots and algae-covered walkways are major slip-and-fall hazards. Regular cleaning mitigates these risks, keeping you compliant with OHS regulations and protecting you from liability.</p>",featured_image:"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1613230902235-eefb7a1cdc48?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80",author:"Exterior Wash QLD Team",date:"2026-05-01",reading_time:6,related_posts:[],faq_schema:[]}];export{e as b};
